The paper proposes a query expansion technique for keyword-based search engines, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a knowledge base, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI) and databases (DB), making cs.AI and cs.DB likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper uses graph analysis to suggest semantically related terms, which is a common technique in machine learning (LG), making cs.LG a possible sub-category.
